<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id79c68b96-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s1847"><num value="1847">§ 1847.</num><heading> Maximum obligation</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The maximum obligation of the Board under all outstanding loans guaranteed by it shall not exceed at any time $250,000,000.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id79c68b97-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/92/70/s8">Pub. L. 92–70, § 8</ref>, <date date="1971-08-09">Aug. 9, 1971</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/85/181">85 Stat. 181</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
